I"	<h3 id="ingredients">Ingredients</h3>
<ul>
  <li>1 LB. BRUSSEL SPROUTS</li>
  <li>2 TBSP OLIVE OIL</li>
  <li>2 TBSP BALSAMIC VINEGAR</li>
  <li>3 GARLIC CLOVES, MINCED</li>
  <li>2 TSP GARLIC POWDER</li>
  <li>SALT &amp; PEPPER TO TASTE</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="procedure">Procedure:</h3>
<ol>
  <li>Preheat grill to 540 F, create a foil boat to hold brussel sprouts on grill.</li>
  <li>Wash and pat dry (wet brussel sprouts will get mushy on the grill) cut each brussel in half through the stem.</li>
  <li>Place brussel sprout in galon bag or bowl, add oil, stir or shake. Then add seasonings , stir or shake.</li>
  <li>Spray foil with non-stick of choice, pour brussel sprouts into foil boat.</li>
  <li>Grill for 10 min, stir. Grill for an addtional 10 to 20 min.</li>
</ol>
